Setting.Name: PartnerSearchCode
Setting.Description: Character string that specifies an OEM Partner Search Code

Setting.Name: CACertificates
Setting.Description: Configure intermediate CA certificates on target device

Setting.Name: ClientCertificates
Setting.Description: Configure client certificates on target device

Setting.Name: RootCertificates
Setting.Description: Configure root certificates on target device

Setting.Name: TrustedPeopleCertificates
Setting.Description: Configure certificates into trusted people store on target device

Setting.Name: TrustedProvisioners
Setting.Description: CA certificates used for provisioning package trust.

Setting.Name: Accounts
Setting.Description: Specify an email account to be automatically set up on the device being provisioned.

Setting.Name: Accounts
Setting.Description: Specify an email account to be automatically set up on the device being provisioned.

Setting.Name: KnownAccountsOEM
Setting.Description: Deploy KnownAccountsOEM.xml file to the device (Ensure file name is KnownAccountsOEM.xml)

Setting.Name: OemFilePath
Setting.Description: Specify alternate KnownAccountsOEM.xml file path

Setting.Name: DefaultAutoConnectOpenState
Setting.Description: If enabled the OOBE Wi-Fi Sense checkbox to automatically connect to open networks will be checked.

Setting.Name: WiFiSenseAllowed
Setting.Description: If enabled the user will be able to opt-in to the autoconnect feature of Wi-FiSense.

Setting.Name: CoexistenceSupport
Setting.Description:
Specifies the type of co-existence supported on the device. Options:
Both: Wi-Fi and Bluetooth both work at the same performance level during co-existence Wi-Fi Reduced: On a 2X2 system, Wi-Fi performance is reduced to 1X1 level Bluetooth centered: When co-existing, Bluetooth has priority and restricts Wi-Fi performance One: Either Wi-Fi or Bluetooth will stop working

Setting.Name: NumAntennaConnected
Setting.Description: Specifies the number of antennas that are connected to the Wi-Fi radio.

Setting.Name: SimultaneousMultiChannelSupported
Setting.Description: Specifies the maximum number of channels that the Wi-Fi device can simultaneously operate on.

Setting.Name: WLANFunctionLevelDeviceResetSupported
Setting.Description: Specifies whether the device supports functional level device reset.

Setting.Name: WLANPlatformLevelDeviceResetSupported
Setting.Description: Specifies whether the device supports platform level device reset.

Setting.Name: Profiles
Setting.Description: Add WLAN profiles to configure wireless connectivity on the target device.

Setting.Name: CountryCodeForExtendedCapabilityPrompts
Setting.Description: Specify a country code for additional capability prompts when apps use privacy-sensitive features (such as Contacts or Microphone). For China, use 'zh'.

Setting.Name: DeviceFormFactor
Setting.Description: DeviceForm specifies a enumeration value that dictates the form factor of the device as reported through telemetry

Setting.Name: MMSMessageRoles
Setting.Description: Message Encryption Negotiation Policy

Setting.Name: NetwpinRoles
Setting.Description: OMA CP Network PIN Policy

Setting.Name: UsernetwpinRoles
Setting.Description: OMA CP User Network PIN Policy

Setting.Name: UserpinRoles
Setting.Description: OMA CP User PIN Policy

Setting.Name: ServiceIndicationRoles
Setting.Description: Service Indication (SI) Message Policy

Setting.Name: ServiceLoadingRoles
Setting.Description: Service Loading (SL) Message Policy

Setting.Name: UpdateManagementServiceAddress
Setting.Description: Update Management Service Addresses by re-ordering and/or removing existing ones

Setting.Name: UpgradeEditionWithLicense
Setting.Description: Enable an edition upgrade of Windows 10 mobile devices. Does not require reboot.

Setting.Name: UpgradeEditionWithProductKey
Setting.Description: Enable an edition upgrade of Windows 10 desktop devices. Requires reboot.

Setting.Name: PublicDocuments
Setting.Description: Add documents to the public profile documents folder on the target device.

Setting.Name: ChinaVariantWin10
Setting.Description: When set to TRUE, only maps approved for China will be used on the device. This key should be set to TRUE on devices intended to be sold in China.

Setting.Name: UseExternalStorage
Setting.Description: When set to TRUE, offline maps will always be downloaded to the device's MicroSD card.

Setting.Name: UseSmallerCache
Setting.Description: When set to TRUE, the map data cache will be limited to 80MB. This key should be set to TRUE on lower end devices with storage limitations.

Setting.Name: EnterpriseModeSiteList
Setting.Description: This setting lets you configure whether your company uses Enterprise Mode and the Enterprise Mode Site List to address common compatibility problems with legacy websites.

Setting.Name: SendIntranetTraffictoInternetExplorer
Setting.Description: Sends all intranet traffic over to Internet Explorer.

Setting.Name: ActiveHoursEnd
Setting.Description: Hour of the day for the end of active hours, where System Updates will not happen automatically.

Setting.Name: ActiveHoursStart
Setting.Description: Hour of the day for the start of active hours, where System Updates will not happen automatically.

Setting.Name: ScheduledInstallTime
Setting.Description: Hour of the day for installs to take place, 0 is midnight.

Setting.Name: DimTimeoutIsManuallySpecified
Setting.Description: Set to True to control the period before the screen dims using the DimTimeout setting, False to allow Windows to automatically select the period based on the screen off timeout

Setting.Name: EnforceConsoleLockScreenTimeout
Setting.Description: Specifies whether the console lock screen timeout should be enforced independently of the user display timeout

Setting.Name: EnforceDisconnectedStandby
Setting.Description: Specifies whether to force the network to disconnect during standby

Setting.Name: HiberFileType
Setting.Description: Specifies the type of HiberFile to be used by the system. Set to 'Reduced' to allow Fast Startup but not Hibernate. Set to 'Full' to allow both Fast Startup and Hibernate.

Setting.Name: IgnoreCsComplianceCheck
Setting.Description: Specifies whether to ignore Connected-Standby compliance checks

Setting.Name: LidNotificationsAreReliable
Setting.Description: Set to True if the platform guarantees that lid notifications will be sent every time the lid is opened or closed. False otherwise

Setting.Name: SmartUserPresenceConfidence
Setting.Description: Specifies the confidence (in percentage) in predicted user-away interval(s)

Setting.Name: CPU
Setting.Description: Specify the parameters needed for CPU power model.

Setting.Name: Display
Setting.Description: Specify the parameters needed for display power model.

Setting.Name: DisplayBacklightPowerFloor
Setting.Description: Specifies display backlight power floor in milli-watts.

Setting.Name: DisplayBacklightPowerGradient
Setting.Description: Specifies display backlight power gradient with respect to brightness.

Setting.Name: DisplayBacklightPowerQDenominator
Setting.Description: Specifies display backlight power's denominator part of the gradient with respect to brightness squared.

Setting.Name: DisplayBacklightPowerQNumerator
Setting.Description: Specifies display backlight power's numerator part of the gradient with respect to brightness squared.

Setting.Name: DisplayPanelPowerAreaFactor
Setting.Description: Specifies display panel power factor for panel area.

Setting.Name: DisplayPanelPowerDpiFactor
Setting.Description: Specifies display panel power factor for display DPI.

Setting.Name: DisplayPanelPowerFloor
Setting.Description: Specifies display panel power floor in milli-watts.

Setting.Name: DisplayPanelPowerVsyncDelta
Setting.Description: Specifies additional display panel power in milli-watts when vsync is on.

Setting.Name: MobileBroadband
Setting.Description: Specify the parameters needed for mobile broadband power model.

Setting.Name: StandbyActivationEnergy
Setting.Description: Specify the parameters needed for standby activation energy model.

Setting.Name: Storage
Setting.Description: Specify the parameters needed for storage power model.

Setting.Name: Wifi
Setting.Description: Specify the parameters needed for wifi power model.

Setting.Name: HeteroDecreaseThreshold
Setting.Description: Processor decrease threshold for individual class1 processors

Setting.Name: HeteroIncreaseThreshold
Setting.Description: Processor increase threshold for individual class1 processors

Setting.Name: ConvertibleSlateModePromptPreference
Setting.Description: Sets the default for hardware-based prompts

Setting.Name: SignInMode
Setting.Description: Specifies whether users switch to tablet mode by default after signing in

Setting.Name: UniversalAppInstall
Setting.Description: Install Universal Applications from the Store or Hosted location

Setting.Name: UniversalAppUninstall
Setting.Description: Uninstall Universal Applications

Setting.Name: UsbErrorsOEMOverride
Setting.Description: UsbErrorOEMOverride Allows a OEM to Hide All USB Device Errors

Setting.Name: WeakCharger
Setting.Description: Enable Weak Charger Notification by Default
